We stop the bleeding at the storage controller, but we start the recovery from a clean-room environment. We don't restore; we reconstruct. Dane, give me a status on the storage controller isolation—is the metadata lock holding?

@all Given the 'poisoned backup' and the ransomware demand, the financial impact has just escalated exponentially. We are no longer just dealing with a data breach; we are dealing with a total impairment of a key revenue-generating asset.

@Che Chang: We are officially over the threshold for a Material Event disclosure. I am initiating the emergency SEC reporting protocol immediately. 

@Dane Stuckey: As we pivot to a clean-room rebuild, I need a granular breakdown of the specific model training logs lost vs. what is recoverable from pre-compromise immutable states. I need to know the exact dollar value of the computing time and R&D hours being written off. We need to be able to justify this impairment to our investors and the SEC. 

